The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Duque of Colombia, Vice President Pence of the United States, and Interim President Guaidó of Venezuela. They discuss their shared commitment to freedom and democracy, their efforts to liberate Venezuela from dictatorship, and their support for President Guaidó as the legitimate leader of Venezuela. They express gratitude for the international support they have received and reaffirm their determination to stand with the people of Venezuela until liberty and democracy are restored.